name: The pathology of being as one is.

metadata.name: Time washes away all wounds.
metadata.description: Heraclitus was right, other waters and yet others go flowing ever on. I have cried a river for each one I ever met, but the stream is ever renewed and today it is in your name that these tears are shed. I bathe in this lake knowing that i will also emerge modified. The becoming will take us to a new anguish tomorrow.
